{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2327","heading":"Definition of rehabilitation for inland waterway projects","label":"2327 Definition of rehabilitation for inland waterway projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/ch36/schV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1992, and not as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1986 which comprises this chapter.","Amendments2014—Par. (1)(E)(ii). substituted “$20,000,000” for “$8,000,000”.Pub. L. 113–121"],"amendments":["Amendments2014—Par. (1)(E)(ii). substituted “$20,000,000” for “$8,000,000”.Pub. L. 113–121"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which consists of structural work on an inland navigation facility operated and maintained by the Corps of Engineers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which will significantly extend the physical life of the feature;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which is economically justified by a benefit-cost analysis;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which will take at least 2 years to complete; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/E/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FE%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which is initially funded before , and will require at least $5,000,000 in capital outlays; orOctober 1, 1994","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/E/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F1%2FE%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which is initially funded on or after such date and will require at least $20,000,000 in capital outlays; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which will enhance the operational efficiency of such component or any other major component of the project by increasing benefits beyond the original project design; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2327/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2327%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"which will require at least $1,000,000 in capital outlays.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
